Parents of interseksualny children can choose "uncertain sex"
Germany became the first European country which recognized the third floor at the children born with external genitals of intermediate type.
The newborn will surely not attribute man's or a female any more.
The new law does not demand from parents to call any sex of such children, allowing parents to specify a floor as "uncertain" or "unspecified" in their birth certificates.
The purpose of the law was to remove pressure from parents who can make hasty decisions on operation on assignment of a floor by the newborn, and counteract discrimination of interseksualny people.
One interseksualny person, according to BBC, told many years later: "I am not a man and not the woman".
I will remain the scrappy product created by doctors with bruises and scars.
About one of two thousand children born annually is not neither the boy, nor the girl.
They have an interseksualnost, one of about 60 pathological states which get under the diagnosis of "violation of sexual development" — the collective term for people with atypical chromosomes, gonads (ovaries or seed plants) or unusually developed external genitals.
Wallis Simpson, perhaps, was interseksualy.
Gender identification is still insufficiently studied, however most of experts in the USA say that if the sex cannot be defined, better to use all available information and to appropriate it, than to wait and trace psychological and physical development of the child before carrying out operation if at all it will occur.
The New York psychiatrist, doctor Jack Dresher who specializes on problems of gender identification, told that the new German law "sounds as good idea".
Interseksualny children create an ethical dilemma.
"Some people have menacing violation lives which demand surgery, however most of children does not have them" — he told.
You can appropriate a floor without operation and then look as the personality develops.
The science how at the child any gender identity will develop, is not too exact.
Nobody can answer questions of why it occurs.
It as a riddle about why people happen gomoseksualna.
The report sent to the European commission in 2011 describes interseksualny people as differing from transsexual or transgender as their state is related not to a gender, and to their biological structure which does not correspond only neither man's, nor to a female, and is typical for both at the same time or is not characteristic for one of them.
These characteristics can be shown in secondary sexual signs, such as the muscle bulk, distribution of indumentum, a breast and a constitution; primary sexual signs, such as reproductive organs and genitals, or in structure of chromosomes and hormones.
The report also adumbrates about discrimination which interseksualny and transgender people in the sphere of employment, and also about the level of oppressions, cruelty and crimes because of prejudices face.
Boys with gender deviations have a special camp now.
Australia and Nepal already allow adults to put man's, female or "the third floor" in the official documents.
In June the 52-year-old inhabitant of Australia Norri Mai-Uelbi became the first-ever person, recognized "sexless", having asserted in court the right for saving of the "uncertain" sexual status for the rest of life.
According to the Ministry of Internal Affairs, in the German passports the third designation in addition to M and F — X, that is interseksualny will be used.
In the next France gender issues still cause contradictions, according to news release on the France 24 channel.
In 2011 tens legislators from France, this pronounced Catholic country, signed the petition about withdrawal of "the gender theory" from school textbooks.
The American Catholic Online website also expressed disagreement with the German law, having written that "in a situation when the world is involved in a new state where the floor is a choice subject, and sexual activity — no, we overturn two more pillars of a civilization".
One mother of the newborn child from Maryland also reported to the Baby Zone website that she would prefer that established to children a floor at the birth.
"To raise the child rather hard and without additional restrictions, especially if you do not know a sex of the child" — she told the website for parents.
Children need stability and confidence.
Historically the children born with male and female genitals were called hermaphrodites — by name beautiful Greek god who possessed signs of both floors.
And more than only ten years ago the medical community perceived a gender as a leaf on which it is possible to erase everything, and then again to draw.
But now many challenge the ethical bases for a surgery, knowing that gender identity is difficult, and doctors sometimes make an incorrect choice, without knowing as the child will perceive the floor appropriated to it when grows.
"In the middle of the XX century it was called as "an urgent psychiatric case"" — Dresher told.
When such children were born, you called not the psychiatrist — you called the surgeon.
The dominating theory how to treat children with genitals of intermediate type, was offered by doctor John Manya from Johns Hopkins University who considered that the gender easily gives in to change.
He introduced the term "gender identity" into circulation and claimed that environment signals, including social — how parents raise the child — interact with genes and the child's hormones, defining, whether the person will consider himself as the man or the woman.
But in one case of 1966 known as "John/Joan", its theories appeared questionable.
He advised the boy's parents, whose penis was injured during negligent trimming, completely to castrate the child, having removed also his small eggs, and to raise it as the girl.
"Manya presented a case as a successful example of transition, but it was not so" — Dresher told.
When the boy was about 15 years old, he again became a boy and married the woman.
But in 38 years he committed suicide.
Dresher told that now some doctors still "apply this model".
But in the 1990th, with arrival of the Internet, the people who endured these operations on change of a floor declared themselves, "dissatisfied with result".
Such is was also Jim Bruce's case, the 36-year-old writer from the State of Montana which was born with man's chromosomes of XY, but genitals of intermediate type.
Doctors could not define precisely, whether there was for it a big clitoris or a small penis, and were convinced that he will never be able to lead "full-fledged life" of the man.
Therefore soon after its birth in 1976 the external genital and Bruce's small eggs were surgically removed, and it was brought up as the girl.
Began to give it female hormones at the age of 12 years.
"I knew that I am not a girl" — he told ABCNews.com.
I was unhappy, but it was very difficult to ask questions.
In 18 years to it the vaginoplastika was appointed.
But being in a depression and understanding that something not so, he demanded medical documentation.
That he learned, was awful.
I was sterilized at the birth, and anybody never told me about it.
Bruce was born with violation of sexual development which did not give it to a body to make enough testosterone for normal development of genitals.
Having learned the truth, he again became a man, receiving pricks of testosterone and having removed the breast.
Operation made it fruitless.
Today he speaks out in defense of others in the organization under the name Interface Project, trying to bring into norm perception of people with an interseksualnost.
But Ann Temar-Mettis, the executive director of the Californian legal association Advocates for Informed Choice, is concerned by that the German law "induces to a naveshivaniye of labels and a stigma".
"Many activists are concerned by that the German law will induce parents to make the hasty decision and to give to the child "uncertain sex"" — she told.
We are afraid that it will promote intervention.
We consider that it is better to appropriate man's or a female, and then to wait.
But we did not see yet how this law, therefore everything will prove that we can do — it to speculate.
Temar-Mettis told that her organization supports the Australian law as "it allows adults to make a choice for the third floor".
"Adults have to have opportunity to make own decisions on a formal sex" — she speaks.
The German law means its assignment at the birth.
This battle which small children should not enter at this stage.
When they grow up, then they will be able to make decisions of rather own body.
But Dr. Arleene Barats, the mammologist-radiologist from Pittsburgh who has a daughter with violation of sexual development and which helps hundreds of other people with support group, told that the German law "will support" both parents, and children.
The daughter Barats, Cathie, was born with man's chromosomes, however it has a violation of sexual development under the name "syndrome of full tolerance to androgens".
As its androgenic receptors incorrectly work, at Cathie female signs developed.
It has a vagina, but there is no uterus and ovaries.
Now, in 29 years, Cathie is married and studies internship in children's psychiatry at university of Pennsylvania.
In spite of the fact that she is infertile, she hopes to become the parent by means of adoption or gestational substitute motherhood.
"The law gives to parents time not to make hasty decisions" — Barats told.
He allows them time to make some analyses and to understand a situation, and also a period before they write "man's" or "female".
In that case you as it should be — raise the child, love the child.
You have a wonderful child, and you feel pleasure.
We do not need to do operation which is irreversible hasty.
"It allows children to participate in the decision and eliminates excitement which moves parents because they do not feel that arrive correctly" — she told.
Eventually the child will solve, with what floor to him or her is more comfortable — and it is remarkable.
It gives to children the chance to make the decision independently.
