The court suspended execution of the decision on practice "to stop-and-search" in the New York department of police
On Thursday the appellate court of the federal district suspended performance of the judicial resolution demanding changes in the stop-and-search program of the New York department of police and discharged the judge of business.
The appellate court of the second district of the USA declared that execution of decisions of the judge Shira Sheyndlin will be suspended before receiving results of the appeal submitted by the city.
In August the judge decided that the city violated the constitution how it carried out the program for street detentions and interrogations.
The city made the appeal complaint to its decision and resolutions on the correcting measures, including the instruction to appoint the controler to help office of police to change practice of work and the related program of training.
On Thursday the appellate court heard debate of the parties on the petition for a business suspension.
The appellate court declared need of removal of the judge because it violated the code of behavior of judges of the USA and was not counted with need to avoid bias demonstration, partially because of an interview series in mass media and the official statements containing the public answer to criticism of court.
The judge decided that police officers violated the civil rights of tens of thousands of people, unreasonably addressing to black and Latin Americans according to the stop-and-search program.
She appointed the external controler for supervision of large-scale changes which include reforms in area the politician, of training and control, and also decided to start the pilot program for testing of the video cameras fixed on a body in those police stations where there is a majority of detentions.
In August New York came to the decision to stop practice of storage of names and addresses of people, put on which were stopped after police check.
Debate on the appeal of the city has to take place after March 14, 2014.
Tactics "to stop and search" was criticized by a great number of lawyers by the civil rights.
"Stop search" practices some decades in this or that form, however the quantity of documentary stops sharply increased at administration of the independent mayor Michael Bloomberg, having reached in 2011 an absolute record in 684 330 people, the majority from which black and Latin Americans.
In 2004 four persons, all — representatives of ethnic minorities, filed a lawsuit the collective claim.
Supporters of changes in the stop-and-search program in the New York department of police say that these changes will put an end to unfair practice, will create more reliable and effective police service and can affect how other departments of police realize this practice.
Opponents claim that changes will reduce fighting spirit of police officers, but not crime rate, will lead to unnecessary expenditure of money and will not solve more global problem of difficult conditions in police because of reduction of number of officers by some thousands for the last decade.
The judge noted that she does not stop practice "to stop-and-search" which corresponds to the constitution, however changes a way with what the New York police stops people.
