"The reason for which we here, consists that the labor government of staff pulled out $430 million from health system" — he told ABC TV TV companies.
When the government of staff tears off nearly half a billion dollars, and the Commonwealth puts 300 million, it is impossible to pretend to be that it is good news.
Mr. Datton asked Mrs. Plibersek to guarantee that any dollar from a saving package will not be spent for additional bureaucracy.
