In October the agency took the 25th place in a rating of attendance of the sites of the Russian mass media according to LiveInternet.
According to the same LiveInternet, the average daily audience of the site rosbalt.ru makes about 150 thousand unique visitors (and to 500 thousand viewings), monthly - about three million unique visitors.
Among the most popular materials for the last five months - a note about helplessness of the Kremlin in the relations with Ukraine, death of the soloist of King and Clown group, riots in capital Biryulev.
The conflict of "Rosbalt" to Roskomnadzor began in July, 2013 when the amendments to the law on mass media which forbade to journalists obscene abuse came into force.
Department found the forbidden lexicon in two videos published on the site of agency ("The Dzhigit from Krasnodar" and "The Pussy Riot was profaned by oil derricks").
Further the parties describe differently.
Roskomnadzor on the basis of the found video records accused "Rosbalt" of rough and systematic violation of the law about mass media and appealed to court with the requirement to select the license at agency.
In "Rosbalt" declared that claims of department are illegal: first, rollers were not an editorial matter, secondly, abusive words in them were disguised, and, thirdly, right after the prevention rollers were removed from the site.
Representatives of agency appealed against claims of Roskomnadzor in world court - and when on October 22, 2013 the Moscow City Court accepted the claim of Roskomnadzor, consideration of these complaints still proceeded.
However already the 25th the magistrate made the decision not in favor of "Rosbalt": the editor-in-chief Nikolay Ulyanov was found guilty of violation of the Code of Administrative Offences and fined 20 thousand rubles - on 10 thousand for each roller.
Obviously, it also predetermined a hearing outcome in Moscow City Court - if to give up thought that the outcome could be predetermined even earlier.
On October 31 the court made the decision to nullify the certificate on registration of "Rosbalt", having actually deprived agency of the status of mass media.
It is impossible to tell that "Rosbalt" during this opposition remained alone.
The agency was supported by deputies of the State Duma (the application addressed to the head of Roskomnadzor Alexander Zharov was signed on October 10 by 26 deputies; the document was filed at the initiative of the CPRF).
Illegality of closing of the edition was declared by the head of the Union of journalists of Russia Vsevolod Bogdanov, the chairman of the Moscow union of journalists Pavel Gusev and the head of the Presidential Council of human rights Mikhail Fedotov.
Moreover, according to Bogdanov, the management of Roskomnadzor even provided it some guarantees of that business will not reach revocation of license.
The trial of "Rosbalt" showed: under whose jurisdiction it is safer to be to mass media in Russia today - a big question.
