Syria destroyed the equipment for the chemical weapon
Syria destroyed all declared capacities for production of the chemical weapon, the Organization for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons recognized.
This first stage of disarmament finished Damascus a day before an established period.
Till November 1 Syria had to destroy the production and other auxiliary objects intended for preparation of fighting toxic agents for application, the BBC reports.
Destruction of reserves of toxic agents or their chemical components has to be complete to the middle of 2014.
According to the representative of OPCW, now toxic agents are in the sealed storages.
The international inspectors went to Syria after on the suburb of Damascus on August 21 during chemical attack were lost, according to the USA, more than 1400 people.
The main task of inspectors was not to waste time - not to allow the Syrian authorities to make more chemical weapon - and to destroy infrastructure for mixing of chemicals and equipment of ammunition.
Now will attentively watch these capacities not to allow their repair.
The following milestone - the middle of November: by this time OPCW and Syrians have to agree on the detailed plan of destruction of already available reserves of toxic agents.
There is a lot of questions.
Where they will be destroyed?
Who will provide for this purpose the equipment?
All Syrian statements will be carefully checked by the western intelligence services.
They with readiness will advise inspectors new objects for check if there are bases to suspect that Damascus is not up to the end frank.
The USA believe that this attack was carried out by active armed forces.
Syria and Russia insist that this work of the Syrian insurgents.
The world community demanded from the Syrian management - according to the agreement reached with mediation of Russia - to destroy or bring into a non-working state all capacities for production of shells, the poisoning gases and liquids and for filling of shells with these substances.
Now, when this stage is passed, destruction of the chemical weapon which is already available for the Syrian army has to become the following step.
It is supposed that in this arsenal there can be more than 1000 tons of the neuroparalytic toxic agents, skin and vesicant mustard gas and other forbidden chemicals which are stored in several tens different places.
It is necessary for its destruction that the OPCW and the Syrian authorities for a start agreed on the schedule of actions - on it two weeks are taken away.
The head of field operations of OPCW Gerry Smith declared the BBC that his inspectors "personally watched destruction of the equipment".
"They have no possibility of a message further production or mixing of the chemical weapon now", - he told.
In the statement of OPCW it is said that inspectors visited 21 of 23 objects in Syria and were convinced that plants on production of shells and toxic agents either are destroyed, or are put out of commission.
The remained two objects are too dangerous to carry out there inspection, it is told in the document, but the equipment from there was transported and checked by specialists of OPCW.
According to Smith, process of destruction of infrastructure on production of the chemical weapon "was especially difficult" as it was necessary to work in the conditions of the proceeding conflict.
At the beginning of October of OPCW received Nobel Peace Prize, however, according to Smith, time to celebrate it at inspectors was not yet - they were too busy.
