Here real European news: the great post-war plan to unite Europe at last stopped.
With eurocrisis the Europe project is officially dead.
In all European Union the parties opposing the EU or for cancellation of euro as single currency gain strength.
Even in Germany the party of eurosceptics "Alternative of Germany" — founded only in this year — appeared from nowhere and received nearly five million votes on September federal elections, thus in fact having forced out "Free democrats" (analog of ours of "Liberal democrats") from the Bundestag.
Always there was an internal opposition to the plan of creation of federal Europe.
Nevertheless the current economic crisis became a turning point.
The austerity measures entered by Berlin and the European central bank and the fetters imposed on national economies through preservation of single currency led many people to thought that the Europe project went too far.
Crisis of euro is a little connected with that the national governments work at excessive budget deficits — it was fair only for Greece.
Actually the eurosystem blocked the members on the exchange rates favorable to the German exporters — that the German politicians and want to keep.
Without possibility of devaluation of national currency Southern Europe appears in in advance unprofitable situation on production capabilities in comparison with Germany.
The only life-saver — to cut down salaries and the public expenditures that is actively supported by Berlin.
Behind the current problems of the budget and currency there is deeper problem of productive abilities of Europe.
As a result of a package of measures on "green" energy, introduced by Brussels — the code meaning subsidizing of the French and German energy companies at the expense of the consumer — the European industry pays twice more for electricity four times more for gas, than in the USA.
It paralizuyushche adverse price conditions as we already saw in Greyndzhmuta.
No freezings of salaries in the world will stop a shattering victory of cheap slate gas of the USA over the European petrochemical industry.
As a result becomes ripe revolt, especially in France, once the most ardent supporter of the EU.
After war the French political elite considered the EU as a way to control Germany and to put Paris on one level with Washington.
But Berlin does not need Paris as in means of obtaining political legitimacy any more, and already imposed own economic policy to Europe, having left the destroyed economy of France in a distress.
Result — the right, opposing the EU Marine Le Pen's party "National front" just won a decisive by-election, having dumped ruling party of socialists on the third place.
"Front" is the most popular party in France with 24 percent of votes now — the timely prevention to the British labourists that it is impossible to proceed from the assumption that split among the right will automatically affect in favor of the left.
What Le Pen with the new found popularity among the French white working class does?
She wants to use elections to the EU next year to create the block in the European parliament against the EU and against single currency.
If — and it is very probable — the parties incited against the EU will get support on these elections, such block will be able to reach for the first time a dominant position in the European parliament.
Here my opinion: soon the growing moods against the EU and against single currency in Europe will merge together to destroy euro.
The EU will not disappear, but it again will become something like indistinct "Europe (sovereign) nations" which was pleasant to General de Gaulle.
Germany and some economies, dependent on it, can keep euro, but France and Southern Europe will restore own currencies.
I assume that Great Britain separates from this project, hoping to approach with the USA.
Nevertheless the growing interest of Washington in the Pacific Ocean indicates probability of that Great Britain will remain unaddressed in cold of Atlantic.
In what situation it leaves Scotland?
We can choose to become the region (in fact) to Small England.
Or we can protect own economic interests that means, in addition, to send Berlin and Brussels to devils.
I suspect that Scotland will be able to succeed within more free European arrangement provided that we will keep the currency.
Cooperation with other countries adherents will be simpler in not federal Europe of the nations.
Otherwise we should consider possibility of repetition of experience of Norway and preservation of our economic independence.
The government of the Scotch national game in Scotland is — strangely enough — the most successful political movement in Europe directed against austerity measures, which received an impressive majority of votes in 2011 thanks to objections against the cuts in expenditure offered (and realized) the labor chancellor of treasury Alistair Darling and the coalition of the Tory and liberal democrats which arose subsequently.
