Early puberty: aging earlier
Afro-American and Latin American girls, as a rule, reach a sexual maturity earlier, than their white contemporaries, show researches.
Physical changes do not mean that puberty is close
There are no certificates of that hormones or other chemicals are guilty
Experts consider that epidemic of obesity can be one of starting mechanisms of early puberty
The tendency to an early sexual maturity is not so expressed at boys
The former correspondent of CNN Pat Etheridge — the journalist specializing on children's health and family questions.
Whether mother should be frightened if at her daughter rudiments of a mammary gland start being formed and raise pubic hair in 7 or 8 years?
At annual conference of the American academy of pediatrics this week to Orlando, the State of Florida, the children's endocrinologist doctor Paul Kaplovitts explained that these early physical changes are quite widespread among the American girls and represent new norm.
"I spend much time, calming parents — usually it does not mean fast approach of a full sexual maturity" — Kaplovitts told.
Obvious signs of development, such as the growing breasts, pubic and axillary hair and a smell of a body, appear at girls earlier.
But there was only a small shift aged to a menarkha (the first periods) for the last four decades.
In the United States middle age makes 12,5 years and decreased in comparison with 12,75 in 1970.
"After the breast starts developing, passes at least two-three years to a menarkha" — Kaplovitts who is also the author of the book "Early puberty at girls told: how to cope with this widespread problem".
Time — the most exact check of how puberty will progress.
Discussion that represents the actual approach of a sexual maturity is conducted, but it is considered "premature" when the increase in a breast is followed by sharp increase in growth till 8 years.
In most cases process will be slowed down or will stop — it that the pediatrician can attentively trace.
Faster progressing can form the basis for analyses at the endocrinologist to exclude serious problems, such as tumors or cysts.
There are procedures to detain early periods and to prevent one more consequence: presenilation of bones which eventually can lead to delay of growth and low growth at mature age.
Recommendations about medicinal or hormonal therapy are based on age of the child, a level of development, growth rates and an emotional maturity.
Psychosocial aspects are also important.
Kaplovitts is careful with drugs, but recognizes that "suppression of puberty can soften behavioural problems and feelings of girls that they differ from contemporaries".
Other big problem is clear: parents simply do not want that their very young daughters had periods.
"They worry about risk of pregnancy or even how they will cope with hygiene questions" — Kaplovitts told.
"It was shock" — one woman at which daughter of periods began in 10 years remembers.
Though there were signs and we spoke about periods, it was not emotionally ready.
It came home from school scared and upset with that it the first among the girlfriends.
There are a lot of advertized theories about the reasons of early puberty.
Nevertheless there are no consecutive proofs of that hormones are guilty of milk or other foodstuff, chemicals in environment or sexual messages in mass media.
At boys — as well as at girls — puberty comes earlier.
Kaplovitts claims that the prerequisite which has the greatest weight, is epidemic of obesity.
In 2001 he helped to conduct research of girls from 6 to 9 years which connects amount of fat in an organism with puberty terms.
Other data confirm this conclusion, but there are a lot of other promoting factors.
In this country Afro-American and Latin American girls, as a rule, reach a sexual maturity earlier, than their white contemporaries.
There are various explanations.
Around the world early puberty is influenced, most likely, by everything: from economic conditions and climate to genes.
Still riddle: though boys have a face hair and on a pubis appear at younger age, the tendency to full early puberty is not so expressed, as at girls.
Other doctors participating in the AAP conference confirmed complexity of this subject.
Emergence of spots and pubic hair meets even at babies and children of yaselny age.
"We have to be careful how we define true approach of a sexual maturity" — Dr. Lawrence Silverman, the children's endocrinologist in children's hospital of Goriyeb to Morristaun, the State of New Jersey told.
Parents should not hesitate to receive the instruction from the pediatrician how to speak with the child.
"It can mean earlier, than it was expected, conversation" — Kaplovitts explained.
If you keep calm, your child, as a rule, will react well.
Girls who blossom early, need confirmation of what even when it occurs before put, this process is a normal part of the life.
