Assad's troops battled some weeks in Safire to insurgents, many of which are connected with groups of Al-Qaeda.
The center declared that on Thursday there were victims from both parties, but did not provide concrete data.
Fights emphasized danger which the chemical weapon inspectors adjusted by tight deadlines of the mission for disposal of Syria of a toxic arsenal in the middle of the proceeding civil war face.
In the statement of OPCW which works in close cooperation with the United Nations, it is told that its team "was satisfied now that it checked and saw destroyed all crucial means of production declared by Syria and the equipment for mixing/gas station".
