Syria submitted the plan of elimination of the chemical weapon which has to be approved next month by the OPCW executive committee.
"I welcome courage and bravery which all of you showed in performance of the most difficult mission ever undertaken by this organization" — the CEO of supervisory group Ahmet Uzyumdzhyu in the comment published by OPCW told.
The third year civil war pushes together insurgents, generally the Sunni Muslims, with Assad's government and his security forces which consist of members of his sect of Alawites, branch of Shiite Islam.
