Whether not clearly, however, Obama knew that his team studied possibility of replacement.
Martin told CNN that he asked Daley, whether the boss of that time knew it about a possible reshuffle.
Though Daley also told that he does not think that the president "was aware" of possible replacement, the former head of administration recognized that, "probably", Obama knew.
Martin added that "Rates are doubled" does not give a definite answer on a question, whether results of political sounding reached Obama's table.
Cooper asked Martin, whether seriously he considers that Obama did not know about research of opportunity to exclude Biden from the electoral list.
"Probably" — Martin answered.
