The profit of Bombardier decreases with falling of deliveries and number of orders for planes
The Bombardier corporation, the Canadian producer of planes and trains, reported on Thursday about reduction of net profit for 15 percent under the influence of the decreased number of orders and deliveries of planes in the third quarter and problems with contracts in its railway division.
The Bombardier company located in Montreal also did not publish any data on flight tests of its latest CSeries plane and did not provide new information on, whether ambitious plans for introduction of the plane to commercial operation by next September will be implemented.
After the first flight of a prototype of the aircraft which took place about one and a half months ago it flew three more time that causes questions of, whether the stage of tests goes according to the schedule.
Results did not justify forecasts and led to falling of actions more than for 8 percent at Toronto Stock exchange.
Cameron Doyerksen, the analyst of National Bank Financial, lowered on Thursday the assessment with "above average market" to "average market" because of belief that growth of actions is limited in the next quarter or two.
"Though decrease in number of deliveries of aircrafts was in general predictable, we are certainly disappointed with indicators of profit of transport department" — Doyerksen in the review of stock market told.
We believe that Bombardier will secure new orders for CSeries in process of continuation of the program of flight tests.
Nevertheless, if in the next months it is not declared new orders, we assume that the market will begin to be skeptical about the program more.
The Bombardier company hopes that the family of the CSeries planes will allow it to win a place in the lower price segment of the market where Boeing and Airbus now dominate.
The first prototype of the aircraft was presented in March and for the first time made flight in September after several months of a delay.
However meanwhile it is not enough firm orders for CSeries — 177 as potential buyers wait for results of flight tests to check statements of the company about fuel efficiency and potential profitability of the new liner.
In total now there are 403 orders and arrangements with 15 clients and operators.
The chief executive officer Pierre Bodoin was sure that Bombardier will achieve the object in 300 firm orders by the time of when the first plane is brought into commercial operation.
On Thursday heads also assured analysts and mass media that the program moves ahead according to the plan.
"The test model of the plane did not remain on the earth more long, than it was expected" — Boduan during telephone conference told, having added that land tests and updatings of the software were planned for an idle time of the plane.
All producers plan tests differently.
We decided to carry out the first flight and to make a break on updatings, so we and arrived.
Will occur so during all program of flight tests.
The second of five test samples has to make flight in the next weeks and all others will soon follow it as the company reported.
And still analysts are skeptical about the statement that the first client will be able to start operation of the CSeries plane in 12 months after its first flight.
The Bombardier company declared that it estimates the term of commissioning and will provide new information in the following some months.
"This slow rate of flight tests - though, most likely, also corresponds to the internal schedule of Bombardier - supports our point of view that commissioning will be postponed for the first quarter 2015" — Doyerksen told.
In the third quarter which terminated on September 30 net income of Bombardier was reduced to $147 million, or 8 cents for an action, from $172 million, or 9 cents for an action, last year.
The corrected earning per share remained former — 9 cents.
The gross income was reduced slightly — from $4,2 to $4,1 billion.
Analysts expected profit of 10 cents on an action and the gross income of $4,56 billion, according to Thomson Reuters I/B/E/S.
The fourth in the world in size the producer of planes reported that he put 45 aircrafts in a quarter that is less than an indicator for previous year — 57.
Total number of orders fell with 83 to 26 planes.
The portfolio of orders of aerospace department made $32,9 billion for September 30, without having changed since December 31.
"In aerospace area results answered our purpose, however the small number of the arriving orders and the general market conditions became an unpleasant factor" — Boduan told.
The gross income in the aerospace direction fell to 13 percent — to $2 billion.
Bombardier, the world's largest producer of trains, reported that the gross income in this sector grew almost by 11 percent — to $2,1 billion.
The portfolio of orders in transport division made $32,6 billion for September 30 that is a little higher than an indicator of December 31.
Problems with execution of several large contracts negatively affected the income of transport division.
The management declared that in the fourth quarter the new development plan will be submitted.
Shares of the company of Bombardier which also declared that the chief financial director of Google corporation Patrick Pichett will be included into board of directors, fell to 8,5 percent — to С$4,83 at the auction in the middle of Thursday.
The Brazilian company Embraer SA, the third in the world in size the commercial producer of planes and the closest competitor of Bombardier, reported on Thursday about reduction of the quarter income by 10 percent.
